df = shapefile_to_annotations(

issue.title: Don't update the dropbox?
issue.body: I've been cleaning up the directories, but if we run rsync, we will just replace all the files i've removed. We need to find a way to rsync only new files? Its very difficult to clean up these data on dropbox without command line tools.

comment.body:
This was a good idea since when we resynced recently it did trampled some of the cleaning that both you and I have done. Sadly this probably includes a bunch of projection and band fixing that I spent a bunch of time on last year (though maybe I actually uploaded those changes to Dropbox?).

Not actively syncing the Dropbox feels hard and suboptimal (what if we legitimately update a file), so I'm wondering if the best route isn't to ensure that the Dropbox version is the version of record (or always the same as the version of record) so that we can sync without worrying about it.

Related: #111 

Thoughts?

issue.title: Check on automated updating
issue.body:
Based on not seeing updates on the website I checked the server today and the data hadn't been updated since June. I manually ran `fill_dir()` which has updated everything, but we need to figure out why the automated updates hadn't worked.

`cron.log` did indicate that things had been run in the last week, but the cronjob itself is under @henrykironde's account so I couldn't look into the details of what is going on. @henrykironde - I'm going to leave this one to you to look into. Let me know if I can be of any help.

The one thing that didn't update (still has write dates from June) is the `data/*_interp.csv` files. @juniperlsimonis - is there something we need to do to trigger those to rebuild once the most recent data is downloaded?
